Description: Essora VM - QEMU Virtual Machine Manager for Essora Linux
 Essora VM is a lightweight graphical frontend for QEMU built with
 Python 3 and GTK3, designed specifically for Essora Linux (Devuan base).
 .
 It allows users to create, configure and run virtual machines without
 using the command line. Each VM is stored as a simple JSON profile and
 disk images are created automatically in qcow2 format using qemu-img.
 .
 Features:
  - Create and manage multiple virtual machines
  - KVM acceleration support with one-click toggle
  - Live screen preview via QEMU monitor socket (screendump)
  - ISO image selection for installation
  - CPU and RAM sliders with real-time values
  - Multilingual interface: English, Spanish, Arabic, Catalan,
    German, French, Italian, Portuguese, Japanese, Hungarian,
    Russian and Chinese
  - Essora branding with custom logo and banner support
  - No system titlebar, centered window, clean dark GTK3 theme
 .
